    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "To anyone who doesn't want the added complexity of maintaining search state and virtual widgets just to get a drawer working w/ React on mobile, Material UI drawer has the ability to hide without unmounting, **so you can use regular refinement lists without any of the workarounds above**. Funny enough, I love Chakra UI and my entire project uses it except for just this single drawer on mobile breakpoints 😝.\r\n\r\nMaterial UI drawer: https://mui.com/material-ui/react-drawer/\r\n\r\n```\r\n<Drawer\r\n  anchor={'left'}\r\n  open={isDrawerIsOpen}\r\n  onClose={handleClose}\r\n  variant=\"temporary\"\r\n  ModalProps={{\r\n    keepMounted: true,\r\n  }}\r\n>\r\n```",
